UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304393283900405
AB  - The paper analyzes the indicator properties of the St. Louis monetary base. It is shown that this base includes a reserve adjustment magnitude which leads to a biased measurement of the total direct contribution of Federal Reserve actions to money growth by making the rate of change of the base directly dependent on the behavior of the public and of commercial banks. Finally attention is drawn to an alternative definition of the monetary base, proposed by Frost (1977), which avoids this defect.
ER  - 

